iStock Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories Warri - Authorities say at least 26 people have died after two buses collided and caught fire on a busy highway in western Nigeria.Oyo state police spokesperson Adekunle Ajisebutu said on Saturday that 11 others were injured in the crash.Police said the two buses were trying to overtake other vehicles on the Lagos-Ibadan Expressway and ended up striking each other.Road accidents are common in Nigeria, where more than 5 000 people died in crashes last year, according to national statistics.Many accidents are caused by reckless driving, while others are attributed to poorly maintained roads and vehicles.24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.